{
  "stem": "18470.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 219.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, when-- he was ill for about a year.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was 15 years old at the time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we didn't quite know what it was.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They diagnosed him with pleurisy, and pleurisy became pneumonia, and then it was an anemia, and then finally we had the-- the dreadful diagnosis.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it took him a year to wind his way out of life, which was a very difficult time for my mother, who kept working throughout that whole period.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I kept going to school and working.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my father was, between hospitalizations, at home.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the hospital experience drained us of our entire savings, and we had to borrow considerable sum of money from relatives.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And finally, my father came home to die.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it was a heart-wrenching experience to see this very vital man just disappear, literally, before my eyes.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the only time I saw him during this whole period-- and it must-- it was part of his illness already when it happened-- really weep was when Franklin Roosevelt died.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was as if he had lost his own father again.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's how reverential he was, and refugees generally were, towards Roosevelt, who was viewed as a savior, a rescuer.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the last two months of my father's life, I left school to take care of-- take care of him personally, and that was a real mitzvah, privilege, for me.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then after he died, my mother became quite ill.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And thereafter, our life changed very dramatically.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I went on to college and semi-professional ball, and eventually she recovered and remarried.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So it was a-- a new chapter in-- in our lives.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I went on to HUC from-- from Brooklyn, and I never thought anything west of Hoboken, New Jersey existed.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Hebrew Union College was quite an experience.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
